*pdf-reader-0.8.6 (24 Sep 2010)

  24 Sep 2010; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org> +pdf-reader-0.8.6.ebuild:
  Version bump. Add ree18 target as well. Don't run tests for jruby since
  they hang, which is not a regression from 0.8.5.

  01 May 2010; Diego E. Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org>
  pdf-reader-0.8.5.ebuild:
  Move to mirrors-only (April 30th had different archives).

  30 Apr 2010; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org> -pdf-reader-0.7.5.ebuild,
  -pdf-reader-0.8.2.ebuild, -pdf-reader-0.8.3.ebuild:
  Remove old versions.

*pdf-reader-0.8.5 (30 Apr 2010)

  30 Apr 2010; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org> +pdf-reader-0.8.5.ebuild:
  Version bump.

*pdf-reader-0.8.3 (14 Feb 2010)

  14 Feb 2010; Diego E. Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org>
  +pdf-reader-0.8.3.ebuild:
  Version bump.

*pdf-reader-0.8.2 (28 Jan 2010)

  28 Jan 2010; Diego E. Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org>
  +pdf-reader-0.8.2.ebuild:
  Version bump, port to fakegem, add support for Ruby 1.9 and JRuby as well.

  27 Dec 2009; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org> pdf-reader-0.7.5.ebuild:
  Fix building with USE=doc -test by always depending on rspec since it is
  required in the Rakefile, fixing bug 298481.

  27 Dec 2009; Hans de Graaff <graaff@gentoo.org> -pdf-reader-0.7.4.ebuild:
  Remove old version.

*pdf-reader-0.7.5 (23 Aug 2009)

  23 Aug 2009; Diego E. Pettenò <flameeyes@gentoo.org>
